# 6. 選択する勇気

Ichika: ♪————!
Ichika: (Miku and the others... They're all listening...)
Ichika: (Come to think of it, we haven't performed with them sitting in front of us for a fairly long time.)
Ichika: (They're usually stuck watching us from somewhere backstage or in the shadow of some piece of equipment...)
Ichika: (We never get to see their faces when we're on stage.)
Ichika: (But they must really enjoy themselves.)
Ichika: (And they've always been there for us. I mean, they helped out so much for our last show, but we never got to thank them properly...)
Ichika: (So... Now's our chance to do that... With our sound!)
Luka: <I can clearly sense what they're all feeling. Maybe far more than during that last show they played...>
Miku: <Me too. The way their sound is resonating with my heart... They're playing for us.>
Miku: <Message received, girls.>
Miku: <And from all of us... Thank you.>
Ichika: ♪————...
Saki: Okay, how'd we do?!
Luka: <Incredibly well... Your performance really resonated with all of us, more than ever before.>
Len: <Yeah, I got goosebumps! This is totally what Leo/need's all about!>
Ichika: That's nice to hear...
KAITO: <All that's left is for you girls to see how it turned out...>
Saki: Huh? For us to see...
Saki: Oh, right! I totally forgot that we're making a video!
Shiho: Oh, Saki... To be fair, I also nearly forgot about our primary goal, but that's a bit much.
Rin: <Let's watch it together! I bet it turned out super duper amazing!>
Honami: Me too. I'm looking forward to seeing how we did.
Saki: Whoa! This is...!
Shiho: Really good... We have so much force behind us, but it's also easy to listen to.
Ichika: I think it's because we got to play for you guys, Miku.
Honami: Thank you all very much...!
Miku: <Hehe. Thank you for the wonderful performance.>
Ichika: Now that I've seen this video... I guess this is what it's like to see us play, huh...?
Honami: I'm actually a bit embarrassed. I have such a serious expression on my face...
Saki: No, don't say that! You looked really cool, Hona!
Rin: <Yeah, totally! It's obvious that you were playing like you meant it, which I think is really good! Sakki on the other hand couldn't contain her joy...!>
Saki: Huh? Me?
MEIKO: <You do always seem to really enjoy yourself, Saki.>
Shiho: That's an understatement. But that's also one of Saki's best qualities. It's nice how the video actually captured that.
Saki: Oh, stop it, you two. You're making me blush... Wait!
Saki: Look, don't forget about Ichi! The way her throat tightens up during the high notes is so cool!
Ichika: Y-You don't have to examine my singing so closely...
Len: <Anyway, now that you're done shooting your video, you just have to upload it, right?>
Miku: <No, don't they have to edit it first?>
Honami: Yes, that's right... Can I borrow a bit more of everyone's time? We should decide on how we want our video to look.
Honami: Which is why I made sure to bring my laptop with me today...
Saki: Whoa, Hona, how did you cram so much stuff into your bag?! Is it enchanted or something?!
Ichika: It must've been heavy. We would've helped if you needed it.
Honami: It's actually not so bad.
Honami: Anyway, I'll send the video over to my computer and load it into my video editing software...
Shiho: Hey, that's a lot easier than I expected...
Rin: <But there's so much going on with her screen. I have no idea what buttons you're supposed to push and stuff...>
Honami: It took me a while to get used to, but I managed to figure some things out by looking up instructions online.
Honami: So, if you click this tab... Oh, here. This lets you easily throw in some really cool effects.
Ichika: ...! Wow! This blur effect goes so well with our performance...!
Len: <That's pretty cool. I didn't realize that one effect could change your video so much.>
Honami: Oh, there's more. For example... We can have flowers bloom as it plays.
Luka: <Oh, that's so cute.>
Shiho: Yeah, it's cute... But it kinda doesn't go with the video, you know?
MEIKO: <It's not exactly a cute and happy song either...>
Honami: Th-This is just a test to show that we have a wide variety of options to choose from.
Ichika: (A wide variety of options to choose from...)
Saki: I see... That's quite the conundrum.
KAITO: <And I have a feeling that it's going to take a while...>
Honami: Actually, it's kind of fun to try all these different things out. Although, that was all just for practice. I'm yet to actually work on an entire video...
Shiho: Yeah, just watching you work is exciting.
Saki: But wow Hona, you really did your homework. You can already do so much after just starting.
Honami: I'm still limited to what a beginner can do... But if you pull this lever-like thing, you can change how the colors look...
Ichika: Oh you're right... It looks a lot darker now.
Honami: Hehe. Isn't this fun?
Honami: When I was at home thinking about how to edit the video, I had the idea to give it a darker tone around the chorus for a more somber feel...
Honami: But I sort of like the original at this point. What do you all think?
Miku: <Both options seem good to me.>
Shiho: Yeah, I thought the same thing. In that case, I guess we should go with the original.
Shiho: This is just me, but I have a feeling that people are gonna focus on how dark it is instead of our song.
Saki: Wait, you think so?! I get what you mean, Shiho, but...
Saki: I really like this dark tone! Like you said, Hona, it goes really well with the theme of the song...
MEIKO: <Looks like we've reached an impasse.>
Honami: What do you think, Ichika...?
Ichika: ... I...
Ichika: (Shiho and Saki both bring up valid points. Neither are wrong.)
Ichika: (This is just like what's going on with my own song... I need to have the courage to make a decision...)
Ichika: (So, I...)
Ichika: I think darker is better.
Ichika: I agree with Saki. It makes it easier to understand what our song's about, and we wouldn't be able to do this if we weren't making a video.
Ichika: Yes, Shiho may be right about people focusing on that more than our song, but I don't think that's necessarily a bad thing...
Ichika: If this effect helps our viewers see how pain and sadness are at the core of this song, then I see no problem with using it.
Honami: Ichika...
Ichika: Oh, of course, Honami... You know the most about video editing here, so you'll have the final say regarding this...
Honami: Thank you. Your suggestions have all been duly noted.
Honami: Both sides provided valid arguments, but I'm of the same mind as Ichika. I think darker is better for this song.
Honami: Since a video can't deliver the impact of a live performance 100%, I'd like to use this effect to achieve something similar.
Shiho: Okay... Maybe I gave our actual song a little too much weight.
Shiho: Also, now that I think about it, not everyone who watches this video is necessarily going to be a die-hard music lover...
Shiho: Which means we should probably keep them in mind if we want them to actually listen to our song. So, let's go with darker.
Ichika: Okay...
Honami: Alright, now that we've reached a consensus, I'll continue working on this when I get home.
Rin: <Cool! I can't wait to see how it turns out♪>
Saki: Just from what you just showed us, Hona, I have a feeling that it's gonna turn out great!
Saki: I'm really looking forward to making even more videos♪
Miku: <Do you know what you girls are going to do for your next video?>
Saki: Yeah, a brand-new song! I'm gonna come up with something really good for everyone who enjoys our music!
Shiho: I know how you feel, but I doubt you're gonna be able to come up with one this instant.
Saki: Y-Yeah, if things go like the one before... I'll have to think about it a lot, which means it might take a really long time...
Saki: But I know that some people out there are really looking forward to hearing our songs, so I'm gonna do everything I can to make sure our next video can bring a new Leo/need song to lots and lots of people.
Ichika: (Oh...)
Ichika: (If I can write songs for us, that would directly help Leo/need...)
Ichika: (Until just recently, I wasn't sure when that was going to be possible, but...)
Ichika: (Things are different now. I have a good feeling about my song...)
Ichika: (I need to complete it as soon as possible, so that the others can hear it.)
